{
  "version": "2.0",
  "category": "MUSICPROD",
  "matchable": false,
  "description": [
    "The music-production taxonomy: a producer's drum-sampler view of a sample, sitting",
    "beside the UCS category on every record. Unlike a UCS category (guessed from the sound",
    "via acoustic signatures), a production role is read from the FILE NAME — a 'Conga' is a",
    "conga because the name says so — so this file carries synonyms and the producer",
    "file-name shorthand, not priors and gates.",
    "",
    "`families` are the top-level groups in display order, each with a colour hue (null = the",
    "grey ramp). `instruments` are matched top-to-bottom, MOST SPECIFIC FIRST, so their order",
    "is match priority and is deliberately NOT the family display order — Kick sits before 808",
    "so 'BD_808' is a kick, 808 before Bass so 'Bass_808' is an 808, Bass before the generic",
    "Perc so 'slap bass' is a bass while a bare 'slap' is percussion.",
    "",
    "Per instrument: `phrases` match as substrings of the normalized name, `abbrevs` as whole",
    "tokens (so 'bd' hits 'BD_01' but not 'bird'). `variations` are curated shades of one",
    "instrument (a snare's rimshot, a hi-hat's closed) and are tried before the base."
  ],
  "families": [
    { "family": "CORE KIT", "hue": 0.02 },
    { "family": "CYMBALS & METALS", "hue": 0.12 },
    { "family": "HAND PERCUSSION", "hue": 0.21 },
